<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./654</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Georgetown</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Brown</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Georgetown</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-28">August 28, 1929</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                    September 17.]</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 212</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to despatch
                                No. 178 of May 27, 1929, file No. 879.6,<note n="32" xml:id="d406fn32">Not printed.</note> regarding the prohibition
                                of flights over French Guiana and to enclose herewith a copy of a
                                letter from His Excellency the Governor of French Guiana dated July
                                30, 1929, and received at this office on August 26, 1929.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harold R.
                                Brown</hi></signed></closer>
                            <pb facs="0717" n="581" xml:id="pg_581"/>
                            <frus:attachment>
                                <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Enclosure—Translation]</seg></opener>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Governor of French Guiana</hi>
                                        (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Siadoies</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American
                                        Vice Consul</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Brown</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cayenne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-30">July 30,
                                            1929</date>.</dateline></opener>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Consul</hi>: In answer to your letter of
                                    April 9, 1929, I have to inform you that I have just granted to
                                    a seaplane of the Pan American Airway a permit to fly over and
                                    land at Cayenne on the study trip the crew of that craft is
                                    taking to South America.</p>
                                <p>I shall look into the application for flight over and landing in
                                    Guiana that may be sent to me by the fliers of the United States
                                    of America for study trips in a friendly spirit.</p>
                                <p>Be pleased [etc.]</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Siadoies</hi></signed></closer>
                            </frus:attachment>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>